<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910107-0077</DOCNO><DOCID>910107-0077.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Belden andamp; Blake Energy Co.:   Firm Acquires 50% Stake   In 96 Ohio Oil, Gas Wells</HL><DATE>01/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BBE TMR</CO><IN>OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Belden andamp; Blake Energy Co. completed the acquisition of a50% working interest in 96 producing oil and gas wells fromEnvirogas Inc., Texas Meridian and certain other interestholders for $325,500.   The North Canton, Ohio, oil company said the remaining 50%stake was acquired by Belden andamp; Blake International Ltd., anindependent limited-partnership company traded on theLuxembourg stock exchange.</LP><TEXT>   The wells, located in Athens County, Ohio, are estimatedto have proven natural gas reserves of 709 million cubic feetof gas and oil reserves of 36,817 barrels.</TEXT></DOC>